{"word":"H5391 - נָשַׁךְ - nâshak - naw-shak' - Bite","slug":"H5391","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָשַׁךְ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâshak"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-shak'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bite"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05DA; - na&#x0302;shak</b> - <i>naw-shak'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>strike</i> with a sting (as a serpent); figuratively, to <i>oppress</i> with interest on a loan: - bite, lend upon usury."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5392\">H5392</a>, <a href=\"#/H5393\">H5393</a>"}]}